        "view": {
          "intent": "node",
          "payload": "node.web.detail"
        },
        "markdown": "# Node Class Demo\n\nThis graph keeps the lesson deliberately small. Import the canonical `node` class through a bridge, inspect the class artifact, then create a local instance yourself. The point is not magic. The point is that a class gives you a reusable starter contract.",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "node-class-demo-declaration"
        }
      }
    },
